Nice intro to basic logic (granted as a Comp-Sci student, was already exposed to a lot of the stuff).  Prof is pretty funny as well (endless bald jokes) and makes lectures entertaining. Course is not difficult at all, probably the easiest course I've had at UTM. If I wasn't being lazy, could have got a 4.0 easily instead of a 3.7 :

God bless this amazing man whom bestowed onto me a 0.3% grade increase which gave me a 3.7 GPA. Greatest professor I've ever had the pleasure of being taught by. Conducts class in a clear and memorable way while being humorous. 10/10 would take again.

Took his PHL145, and overall i really enjoyed the class. The course material itself is interesting given that it makes sense, however you will find that sometimes there are certain aspects which take a while to make sense. The good news is that Professor Charlow really makes an effort to be clear and really shows an effort for students to succeed.
Ok prof. does try content sometimes interesting not a bird course did study from practice problems but didnt well on midterm or exam even though I understood the topics.

rComments: THIS GUY IS AN AMAZING PROF!!! coming from a person who failed this course and did it again with Charlow, he really made it bearable, fun & comprehensive. I thought it would be an up hill battle of HATING THIS COURSE - but with a surprising twist it became one of my favorite phl courses i'd ever take. If you're reading this nate, thank you so much!

Not a bad prof. tries to explain concepts some say its a bird course but didnt find that found homework hard, has a midterm and exam studied from practice problems and didnt do well even though I understood most of the topics. Pretty good overall though.

rComments: Nate's class was one of the best structured courses that I have ever taken. He structured the class a little more differently than one would a general interest epistemology class and this was to his advantage - the issues we looked at were both historical and relevant at the same time - no reading felt like it was forced for the sake of tradition.

his lectures are a bit dull but it's philosophy so he doesn't exactly have a lot to work with. as for the difficulty it's fairly easy. as for him he's a very nice and caring guy, he's also pretty funny
Of all the classes, my best mark was from Nate's course. He is very helpful and very enthusiastic in making sure his students have a clear understanding of the course material. He is also super cool.

He is a great prof, but I didn't like the class. I took this class in my final year (hoping it was going to be okay), and I started off pretty well with A-A+, but his online quizzes were tough and the exam was a disaster!! Yet to find out my final grade...
Good guy. Explains concepts well, classes can get slightly dull if noone bothers to participate. marks fair but easy insofar as the course requires it.

dont really know why i took the class but he made it worth it. hes knowledgable and clear about whatever it is that he goes on about, engages the class which is always a good thing,and is very helpful and sweet

So i went into PHL333 DREADING IT (as I took the course before and failed).  By the end of Nate's course, PHL333 became my favorite class - Charlow actually made me excited and interested in it! I actually semi-enjoyed writing essays. As a result, the interest he inspired enabled me to learn and grow from this course. I love Charlow; he is awesome

Make sure you have plenty of energy for his class. I have lost track of the times I fell asleep in his class. The content itself isn't even that bad; he's just a dull speaker. You better bring your own motivation if you wanna succeed in his class.

I was in the first lecture he ever taught, and at first I was not impressed. However, over time he improved, and I found him to be very interesting and funny. By the end I had a much greater understanding of philosophy, and overall, enjoyed the course.
Great professor, fascinating dude.

Dr. Nate Charlow is an excellent professor, and funny lecturer. He's also nice and helpful. It helps that he's really passionate about what he's teaching and coming from a philosophy dork, he knows his stuff. Relevant assignments and awesome readings. Dr.Charlow is awesomeeeee :)

Took course jus for the distribution requriment thing, and this is the best course I have taken. He is funny, helpful, and the most normal prof meaning the vocabulary he uses is like a really smart student teaching other students. Take this course with prof charlow and attend lectures he turns the textbook gibberish to english!
Charlow, if you are reading this: Speak up! Drink coffee before the lectures or something. Philosophy is AWESOME.Otherwise, interesting and intelligent prof; very good and insightful.
Prof. Charlow should excite the students more. Debates are exciting. Opinions are exciting. Not dry stuff...

He's quite funny actually, not too dry. the only thing that'd be of help is probably posting the weekly assignments a bit earlier. His lectures are definitely worth going of if you don't understand the readings,  took the course for no reason, now I'm thinking of minoring in it.

Dr. Charlow's an awesome professor! He can be sidetracked at times, but he genuinely cares about and considers almost all student. I enrolled as an elective/general interest but his course has inspired me to continue philosophical studies, perhaps even major.

Professor Charlow is quite soft - spoken and it is apparent in the expression of his students while he teaches. Granted, it is his first year of teaching at UTM, but we couldn't have asked for a drier teacher. He even gives us attitude when things don't go his way (leaving the class early etc.) I don't recommend taking this course if he's teaching.
Pretty cool. Wish he was more clear and systematic.
